            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Hd1e108">Rubrica 3</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De affectibus et motibus animorum</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>
      ¶ De affectibus et motibus
      <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>animorum. Rubrica. 3
      
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e121">
               <lb ed="#V" n="24"/> <ref>IN genell. ca. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e125">Sub
        <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>te erit ar
        <lb ed="#V" n="26" break="no"/>petitus peccati: et tu dominaberis il
        <lb ed="#V" n="27" break="no"/>lius. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e135"> /
       <ref>c. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e137">Sensus et cogitatio hu
        <lb ed="#V" n="28" break="no"/>mani cordis in malum prona sunt ab adole
        <lb ed="#V" n="29" break="no"/>scentia sua </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e146">
               <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>
            ¶ <ref>Oratius epistolarum. e. 2. lib. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e150">Animum
        <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>rege: qui nisi paret Imperat: hunc frenis hunc
        <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>tu compesce cathenis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e158">
               <lb ed="#V" n="33"/>
            ¶ <ref>Quintilianus declama. 9 declam.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e162">Quic
        <lb ed="#V" n="34" break="no"/>quid rationem vincit affectus est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e168">
               <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>
            ¶ <ref>Seneca in epistolis ad lucillum: libro. 11
        <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>c. 3. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e172">Facilius est initia affectuum prohi
        <lb ed="#V" n="37" break="no"/>bere quam impetum regere. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e180"> /
      <ref>Libro. 19. c. 10.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e182">Imbecillis est primo omnis affectus: dein
        <lb ed="#V" n="39" break="no"/>de ipse se concitat et vires dum procedit pa
        <lb ed="#V" n="40" break="no"/>rat: excluditur facilius quam expellitur. Quis
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>negat omnes affectus a quodam quasi na
        <lb ed="#V" n="42" break="no"/>turali fluere principio.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e196"> ¶
      <ref>Idem de reme
        <lb ed="#V" n="43" break="no"/>diis fortu. c. 21. et fi</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e198">Facilius reges animum
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>nulla vanitate rerum tumentem.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e206"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e208">Idem <!--no ref-->
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>de moribus: hoc habet omnis affectus: vt <!--65.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>in quo insanit ceteros furere putet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e221">
               <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>
            ¶ <ref>Ambrosius de officiis lib. i. ca. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e225">Affectus
        <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>nature est non potestatis. Etsi vis quedam
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>nature in omni appetitu sit: tamen idem ap
        <lb ed="#V" n="50" break="no"/>petitus rationi subiectus est legi nature ip
        <lb ed="#V" n="51" break="no"/>sius: et obedit ei. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e237">
               <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>
            ¶ <ref>Boetius in musica. ca. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e241">Ut sese corporis
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>affectus habent: ita etiam pulsus cordis. mo
        <lb ed="#V" n="54" break="no"/>tibus incitantur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e249">
               <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>
            ¶ <ref>Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 6. c. 24. et pe.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="56"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e253">Ratio motus vestros componat.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e259">
               <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>
            ¶ <ref>Gregorius in pastorali. c. 12.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e263">Humanum
        <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>quidem est in corde tentationem perpeti: de
        <lb ed="#V" n="59" break="no"/>moniacum vero est tentationis certamie in ope
        <lb ed="#V" n="60" break="no"/>ratione superari. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e273">
               <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>
               ¶ <ref>Isidorus soliloquiorum li. 2. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e277">In ini
        <lb ed="#V" n="62" break="no"/>tio resiste cogitationi pessime. Si titilat pra
        <lb ed="#V" n="63" break="no"/>ua cogitatio non consenties illi. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e285"> /
       <ref>.c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e287">Pri
        <lb ed="#V" n="64" break="no"/>mam peccati suggestionem contere: vt non
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>sinas eam in corde tuo manere. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-d1e296"> /
       <ref>c. 21.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14369-Qd1e298">Co
        <lb ed="#V" n="66" break="no"/>hibe animi motus. </quote>
            </p>
